    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup anchored by three high-upside plays exceeding the 69-point mark. **Junior Caminero** leads our ranks with a 76.66 score, bolstered by favorable wind conditions and a solid matchup against Keller. He is closely followed by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (75.48), whose dynamic platoon edge against Myers makes him an elite start despite batting eighth. While the catcher position is often volatile, **Dillon Dingler** (48.35) remains a necessary fixture; despite facing the formidable Crochet, his dynamic platoon advantage (L) provides enough of a floor to keep him in the C2 slot. We are also monitoring **Chase Meidroth** (66.48) and **Trea Turner** (69.15), both of whom benefit significantly from their leadoff spots, maximizing their opportunities to pad our stolen base and run totals against their respective opponents.\n\nStrategic benching remains critical to our game cap management. **Josh Smith** was the most difficult exclusion today, landing at a 40.62 score. While he holds a strong platoon advantage against Woo, he ultimately lost his spot to the more efficient top-of-the-order production from **Carson Benge** (63.27) and the elite xwOBA profile of **Yordan Alvarez** (67.90). We continue to keep a close eye on our depth, as **Christian Yelich** remains on the IL, **Colt Keith** sits on the bench due to rest/lineup status, and **Zac Veen** remains in Albuquerque, leaving us to rely on our active core to handle the heavy lifting.\n\nManagers should be wary of the volatility surrounding **Hyeseong Kim** (57.88). While he enjoys a 14% boost from park factors, his poor BvP history (41 PA) against Lorenzen introduces significant risk, making him a marginal play today. Furthermore, while we are pleased to deploy **Victor Scott II** (47.23) for his speed, his late-order placement and sub-par SP matchup dampen his efficiency. Ensure that **Kyle Schwarber** (66.04) is locked into your OF1 slot; his elite 0.402 xwOBA against Holmes provides the highest consistency among our outfielders, effectively neutralizing the risk of a sub-optimal SP_xERA matchup.",
